The paper presents a novel algorithm for deep reinforcement learning that optimizes an ensemble of policies to solve complex tasks with high initial state variation. This approach involves dividing the initial state space into different slices and gradually unifying them into a single policy. Given the focus on deep RL and optimization of policies, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves tasks related to robotics (grasping, manipulation, and locomotion), which suggests sub-categories such as cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves tasks related to computer vision (e.g., object recognition), which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques to solve complex tasks, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category.
